The students obtain methods of heritage language fieldwork, i.e. skills of oral interviewing and sound recording. They are dealing with collecting and transcribing dialect data, and they present it as required.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The target of the course is to get acquainted with one of the Estonian regional heritage language, with the help of thetextbook of Estonian dialects; learning to collect and record heritage language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows and is able to notice the peculiarities of the heritage language spoken in the area of practice. The student is able to make contact with the informants and to interview the informants according to the interview plan, recording the material with a dictaphone. The student is proficient in phonetic writing and is able to write down the recorded text in phonetic transcription.
